ðŸ› ï¸ Skills Demonstrated
bash
# Basic firewall rules
iptables -I INPUT -p tcp --dport 31337 -j DROP
iptables -I INPUT -p udp --dport 31337 -j DROP

# Specific host filtering
iptables -I INPUT 1 -p tcp -s 10.0.0.2 --dport 31337 -j ACCEPT
iptables -I INPUT 2 -p tcp -s 10.0.0.3 --dport 31337 -j DROP

# OUTPUT chain control
iptables -I OUTPUT 1 -p tcp -d 10.0.0.2 --dport 31337 -j ACCEPT
iptables Mastery - Linux firewall configuration and management

Packet Filtering - Controlling network traffic based on various criteria

Rule Prioritization - Understanding rule order and chain processing

Network Access Control - Implementing security policies through filtering

Traffic Monitoring - Network observation and analysis techniques

Security Policy Implementation - Translating security requirements to firewall rules

